events.description: Come join us at High-Hand Brewery to hear a live performance by Steve Price’s All-Star Band — A Night of AWESOME Music with an All-Star Lineup! Expect an amazing night of live music featuring local favorite Steve Price, founding and current drummer for the legendary band Pablo Cruise. Leading the evening is the Steve Price All-Star Band, a high-energy, ever-evolving group of exceptionally talented musicians. With a rotating lineup, every show is a fresh and exciting experience. Enjoy a wide range of musical styles—from smooth Yacht Rock grooves to beloved Classic Rock favorites—delivered by musicians who truly know how to bring the party. This special performance also features an incredible lineup of guest artists, each bringing their own unique sound and personality to the stage: Jon Pauling – A Christian artist whose music transcends genre and audience, connecting effortlessly with both Christian and secular listeners through soulful, inspiring performances. Rick Turnage – A highly accomplished guitarist and vocalist with 48 years of professional experience, Rick is known for his smooth, polished guitar style and his natural ability to connect with any audience, delivering a refined and entertaining performance every time. Dana Moret – This “little Creole girl” LOVES the Blues! An amazing vocalist, Dana has shared the stage with several of her musical influences, including Lydia Pense and Cold Blood, Big Brother and the Holding Company, John Lee Hooker Jr., the legendary Guitar Shorty, and Terry Evans, and regularly performs with Mick Martin and the Blues Rockers featuring Tim Barnes. Ellen Range – Another incredibly talented and fabulous vocalist, Ellen is a true local favorite, known for her powerful voice and captivating stage presence. Set in the inviting atmosphere of High-Hand Brewery, this night promises great music, great energy, and great craft beer. Don’t miss this unforgettable evening of world-class talent and local favorites all on one stage. Only guests 18 and older may attend our “On Stage” concerts.

When you arrive, find Melissa to sign up and lock in your spot. High-Hand’s pro backline will be ready for you. Solo players will be paired up into spontaneous jam groups, and together you’ll decide what to play—keeping it loose, creative, and fun. It’s all about rocking out, connecting with fellow musicians, and celebrating the amazing music community we’re surrounded by. Each week will also feature a guest band to keep the night energized and inspiring. Come jam, hang out, and make your Wednesday groove. Only guests 18 and older may attend our “On Stage” concerts.
